# Vendored upstream: the skill-creator harness this plugin WRAPS (winner #9).
#
# We do NOT fork skill-creator. Forking would silently absorb every upstream
# behavior change into our tree the next time someone merged, and there'd be no
# single line to point at that says "this is the version we build on." Instead we
# pin it to an exact commit and wrap it. An upstream improvement then becomes a
# one-line SHA bump here — reviewable in a diff, revertible in a revert — not a
# merge. See ../references/skill-iteration.md for how the wrap composes with the
# file-based handoff seam and the advisory delta gate.
#
# To bump: set `sha` to the new commit, refresh `retrieved`, note what changed in
# the commit message, and re-run the plugin-factory cheap pack — it asserts this
# file still parses and that `sha` is a full 40-hex commit id (a branch name or a
# short sha here is a silent drift waiting to happen, so the gate rejects it).
#
# Fields are `key: value`, one per line. Lines starting with `#` are comments.
repo: anthropics/skills
path: skills/skill-creator/
ref: main
sha: 9d2f1ae187231d8199c64b5b762e1bdf2244733d
retrieved: 2026-07-10
